arch farmer
name Alan
msg
@match hi|hello|hola|hey
Hello there, stranger. What brings you to our abode? The crops aren't ready to harvest yet.
@match farm|crops
We got a warm snap at the start of the growing season and were able to plant early.
Combine that with the regular rain we've had, and it's looking like a bumper crop this year.
@match grow
The soil here's very fertile. Some of the best farmland on Bigworld. With the right rain, you could grow anything in these fields.
@match food
We surely wouldn't let you leave on an empty stomach! We may not have much, but we can at least feed you.
@match soil|dirt
The soil is dark and full of organic matter. Seems to be washing down the mountains this way; something big must've died up there a while ago.
@match died
I dunno what would've died up in the hills to make this must farming dirt, but I ain't complaining.
@match cold|door
It does get cold in the winter without a door, but the stove gets pretty hot, so we manage.
@match Christopher
Aye, we go way back. Both grew up out here on these very fields.
@match Turing
Turing? Didn't that fella have a machine that could do anything? Some wizardry if you ask me.
@match rose
The rose? That was, uh, a gift from ah, a friend. A lover, of sorts.
*Alan and Christopher make eye contact*
@match lover
Aye, we're close, very close.
@match close
We see each other every day, so we know a lot about each other.
@match girl
*Alan looks confused for a brief second, then regains composure*
You seem intent on figuring out my lover. I suppose I can tell you.
*Alan inhales*
Christopher and I are lovers.
He gave me the rose.
It's why there's only one bed.
It's why there's the odd arrangement of food out back.
@match roommate|hut|house
The place is big enough for two people, why not have two people live in it? Chrissy and I decided we could be roommates.
*Christopher scowls at being called "Chrissy"*
@match bed
What about the bed?
@match gay
Yeah, we are.
If you see us as less for it, that is a problem with you, not a problem with us.
endmsg
